body:
> You'll see the word Mul not Multiply.

Yes. But at the point when this replacement is run, it's already been switched to `Multiply`, or there wouldn't be the trailing "tiply". Also, look at the [c api doc for the op](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/cc/class/tensorflow/ops/multiply)

same for [`Sub`](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/core/api_def/base_api/api_def_Sub.pbtxt), and it's [generated docs](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/subtract), the only reason it didn't fail the same way is that it had the back-quotes in the replace string.

So I think this is correct.
